(113, 3, '', 12, 4, 'Such is Life', '', '2009', '7 MIN', 'Digibeta', 'Stephen Godfrey', 'Stephen Godfrey', 'Stephen Godfrey', 'Paul Walker', '', '', 'A true story about life and the world we''ve created, where contact is without face and how; even in death you can still exsist. \n', 'The debut screening of this film by writer/director Stephen Godfrey. DOP Paul Walker was involved in Academy Award Nominated ‘Philip Glass’ Documentary.  \n', 'Such_is_Life_S.jpg', 'Such_is_Life_S.jpg.jpg', 1, '2010-04-26 19:18:58'),
(114, 3, '', 12, 5, 'Pests', '', '2008', '14:30 MIN', 'Digibeta', 'Kate Breen', 'Tim Dean', 'Tim Dean', 'Simon Ozolins', 'Daniel Fredriksen, Molly Knight, Roger Oakley', '', 'Who is the pest? Is it the outsider, the unknown, or is it a little closer to home?', 'Funded under the FIlm Victoria Propeller Shorts initiative in 2008. Writer/Director Tim Dean has won numerous prizes (including four Tropfest awards in 2009) for his most recent film Fences. \n', 'Pests_S.jpg', 'Pests_LL.jpg', 1, '2010-04-26 19:20:13'),
(115, 3, '', 12, 6, 'Jacob', '', '2009', '11 MIN', 'Digibeta', 'Darren Dale, Rhea Stephenson', 'Dena Curtis ', 'Dena Curtis ', 'Murray Lui', '', 'Ningali Lawford-Wolf, Connie Amos, Heath Bergersen, David Ngoombujarra, LeRoy Parson', 'Gina, a young Aboriginal mother finds herself in a predicament when her husband Max returns home and learns the truth about baby Jacob.\n', 'Screening premiere - Message Sticks Indigenous Film Festival, 2009. MIFF- Accelerator Program 2009, Adelaide Short Films Festival- won Best Short, ImagiNATIVE Film Festival Toronto, WOW Film Festival - Best Film, Most recently Aspen Short Film Festival 2010 - Competition\n', 'Jacob_S.jpg', 'Jacob_LL.jpg', 1, '2010-04-26 19:21:34'),
(116, 3, '', 12, 7, 'The water was dark and it went forever down', '', '2009', '11:13 MIN', 'Digibeta', 'Kate Beverley', 'Khrob Edmonds, Miranda Edmonds', 'Khrob Edmonds, Miranda Edmonds (based on a short story by Tim Winton)', 'Katie Milwright', '', 'Madeline Wallman, Anna Brockway', 'During a holiday at the beach a young girl tries to escape the drowning influence of her alcoholic mother. She swims to an island inhabited only by birds, it is there she realises that only the strong survive.\n', 'Premiered at the Rhode Island International Film Festival 2009 and has since played to audiences in Ireland, Croatia, South Africa, Turkey, Canada and Australia. Based on a short story of the same name by author Tim Winton, this uniquely West Australian piece has stunned audiences with its visual beauty and haunting narrative. \n', 'The_Water_Was_Dark_S.jpg', 'The_Water_Was_Dark_S.jpg.jpg', 1, '2010-04-26 19:22:33');
