(2, 5, 'german-films', 'German Films', '<p><span class="whiteheader">German Films </span></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p><em>A selection of films from the German competition at the 2009 interfilm Berlin Short Film Festival.</em><br />\n</p>\n<br />\n<p>\nTHE PALACE GEORGE CINEMAS</p>\n<p class="uppercase">133-135 fitzroy st, st kilda <br />\n</p>\nWEDNESDAY 26 MAY, 7.30PM - 9PM<br />\n<br />\nEach year interfilm Berlin receives around 800 entries for its German competition. This selection of fiction, documentary and animation from the 2009 Festival provides a snapshot of contemporary German short production and includes the Titelbild Award winning<em> Bes</em>.<br />\n<br />\n<p>\nCurated by: Alexander Stein, Sophie Werner and Matthias Groll – interfilm Berlin Short Film Festival</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2010-04-23 12:08:18', '2010-05-18 09:19:26'),
(3, 5, 'dutch-films', 'Dutch Films', '<p><span class="whiteheader">Dutch Films</span></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p><em>A selection of films from the ‘Focus On: the Netherlands’ program at the 2009 interfilm Berlin Short Film Festival</em><br />\n</p>\n<br />\n<p><span class="uppercase">The Palace George Cinemas</span></p>\n<p class="uppercase">133-135 fitzroy st, st kilda <br />\n</p>\n<span class="uppercase">\n</span>SUNDAY 30 MAY, 4.30PM - 6PM<br />\n<br />\nThe Netherlands has a rich history of diverse filmmaking, encompassing socially analytical documentaries, colourful animations and moving dramas. This program includes the 2009 Berlin-Brandenburg Short Award Best Film winner, <em>Missen/Missing</em>, as well as the winner of the interfilm Documentary Prize, <em>Grijsgedraaid/Grey Matter</em>. <br />\n<br />\n<p>Curated by: Romy Albers and&nbsp; Maike Lasseur – Film Museum Amsterdam</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2010-04-23 12:08:29', '2010-05-18 09:20:20'),
(4, 5, 'berlin-the-wall-beyond', 'Berlin: The wall & Beyond', '<p class="whiteheader">BERLIN: THE WALL AND BEYOND</p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p><em>&nbsp;A selection of films from the ‘CLOSE UP - Eastern Front / Western Front’ program at interfilm Berlin 2009 Short Film Festival – marking the 20th anniversary of the fall of the Berlin Wall</em><br />\n<br />\n</p>\n<p>\nTHE PALACE GEORGE CINEMAS</p>\n<p class="uppercase">133-135 fitzroy st, st kilda<br />\n</p>\n<p>\nFRIDAY 28 MAY, 7.30PM - 9PM<br />\n<br />\nThe Berlin Wall marked a manacing borderline that cut through the city for 28 years; freedom and democracy on one side, social achievements and proletariat dictatorship on the other. It symbolised both the division of Germany as well as the state that entrenched itself behind it. &nbsp;<br />\n</p>\n<p>\n</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This program follows the different strategies of truth and conviction during the existance of GDR and beyond the time the Wall fell. The films deal with the power and powerlessness of both the Stasi (Ministerium f&#252;r Staatssicherheit/ Ministry for State Security - East German Secret Police) and individual people. </p>\n<p>\n<br />\n&nbsp;</p>', '2010-04-23 12:08:54', '2010-05-18 09:19:02'),
(5, 5, 'french-films', 'French Films', '', '2010-04-23 12:09:06', '2010-04-23 12:09:06'),
(6, 8, 'tickets', 'Tickets', '<p><span class="whiteheader"><span class="whiteheader">TICKETS</span></span><span class="whiteheader">\n<hr />\n</span>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="uppercase"><em>As films featured in the St Kilda Film Festival are unclassified, </em></p>\n<p><em class="uppercase">persons under 18 years of age will not be admitted. </em></p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt" class="orangeheader">FILM BUFF’S FEAST </span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><em>The complete degustation</em> - your pass to all St Kilda Film Festival sessions. Sample all Top100 Films and Festival screenings with the Film Buff’s Feast^. (Excluding Opening Night, Closing Night Awards and sessions at The Dogs Bar).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>$93 Full/ $82 Concessions*</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Film Buff’s Feast^ can be purchased from&nbsp;<span style="color: #ffffff"><a href="http://www.palacecinemas.com.au/festivals/stkildafilmfestival2010/" target="_blank">The Palace George Cinemas Box Office</a> </span>from 5 May – 25 May, and from the VIP Ticketing Desk at The Palace George Cinemas from 26 May to 30 May.<br />\n</p>\n<hr />\n<span style="font-size: 12pt" class="orangeheader">MID-WEEK MIX </span>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><span class="uppercase">Wednesday 26 &amp; Thursday 27 May</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Liven up your Wednesday and Thursday with the Mid-Week Mix^</em> - your ticket to all St Kilda Film Festival sessions and events mid-week, including the fantastic SoundKILDA. </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>$44 Full/ $35 Concessions*</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Mid-Week Mix^ can be purchased from <span style="color: #ffffff"><a href="http://www.palacecinemas.com.au/festivals/stkildafilmfestival2010/" target="_blank">The Palace George Cinemas Box <span style="color: #ffffff"></a><a href="http://www.palacecinemas.com.au/festivals/stkildafilmfestival2010/" target="_blank">Office</a><a href="http://www.palacecinemas.com.au/festivals/stkildafilmfestival2010/" target="_blank"> </a></span></span>from 5 May – 25 May, and from the VIP Ticketing Desk at The Palace George Cinemas from 26 May to 30 May.<br />\n</p>\n<hr />\n<span style="font-size: 12pt" class="orangeheader">SINGLE SESSION </span>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p>Pick the session that suits you.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>$15 Full/ $12 Concessions* <br />\n</p>\n<hr />\n<span style="font-size: 12pt" class="orangeheader">SOUNDKILDA </span>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><span class="uppercase">Thursday 27 May, 9PM<br />\n</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>The way music videos were meant to be seen – loud and large on the big screen.</em> </p>\n<p>Spicks and Specks music guru Alan Brough returns as host. </p>\n<p>Find out who is crowned the best at the awards and then help them celebrate at the exclusive and official after party. </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>$25 Full/ $20 Concession* </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u><a href="http://www.stkildafilmfestival.com.au/page-39/view-session"><span class="uppercase">click here to view session</span></a></u><br />\n</p>\n<hr />\n<span style="font-size: 12pt" class="orangeheader">OPENING NIGHT </span>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><span class="uppercase">Tuesday 25 May, 7.30pm</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Walk the red carpet at St Kilda’s iconic Palais Theatre to open the 2010 St Kilda Film Festival. Featuring a taste of what’s to come for the rest of the Festival – a selection of the best Australian shorts, along with some international surprises. The ultimate pass for film fanatics. <br />\n<br />\n</p>\n<p>$30 Full/ $25 Concessions* </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Opening Night tickets are available from <span style="color: #ffffff"><a style="color: #ffffff" href="http://www.palacecinemas.com.au/festivals/stkildafilmfestival2010/" target="_blank">The Palace George Cinemas Box Office</a><a href="http://www.palacecinemas.com.au/festivals/stkildafilmfestival2010/" target="_blank"></span>&nbsp;</a>. Limited tickets on sale. </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><u><a href="http://www.stkildafilmfestival.com.au/page-20/opening-night"><span class="uppercase">click here for opening night session details</span></a></u><br />\n</p>\n<hr />\n<span style="font-size: 12pt" class="orangeheader">CLOSING NIGHT AWARDS</span>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<p><span class="uppercase">Sunday 30 May, 8.30pm</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Celebrate as we wrap up the St Kilda Film Festival for yet another year. Join in the excitement as the best of this year’s filmmakers are awarded over $40,000 of cash and in-kind prizes. </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>$25 Full/ $20 Concession*</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Closing Night tickets are available from the Festival VIP Ticketing Desk at The Palace George Cinemas, during the Festival. Cash sales only. </p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="uppercase"><u><a href="http://www.stkildafilmfestival.com.au/page-48/closing-night-awards">click here for more information about closing night </a></u><br />\n</p>\n<hr size="2" width="100%" />\n<strong><em>* CONCESSION</em></strong><br />\nConcession applies to full time students, recipients of the Australian Social Security Pension, Victorian Seniors Card holders, aged pensioners, film industry concession card holders, Triple R Subscriber Card holders and Palace Movie Club Members.<br />\n<br />\n<em><strong>^ FILM BUFF’S FEAST &amp; MID-WEEK MIX PASSES</strong></em><br />\nThe Film Buff’s Feast and Mid-Week Mix passes are not tickets to entry. Pass holders must redeem their passes at the Festival VIP Ticketing Desk for a session specific ticket.<br />\n<br />\n<em><strong>SEATING &amp; ACCESS</strong></em><br />\nAll seating at St Kilda Film Festival screenings is general admission. Latecomers will not be admitted until a suitable break in the screening.<br />\n<br />\nThe Palace George Cinemas is wheelchair accessible. Please contact The Palace George Cinemas on (03) 9534 6922 for full details.<br />\n<br />\nThe St Kilda Film Festival welcomes holders of the Companion Card to attend Festival screenings. <br />\n<br />\n<em><strong>REFUND/ EXCHANGES</strong></em><br />\nAll tickets are sold on a no-refund, exchange or cancellation basis. Lost or stolen tickets will not be replaced or refunded.<br />\n<em><strong><br />\nCLASSIFICATION NOTICE</strong></em><br />\nAs films featured in the St Kilda Film Festival are unclassified, persons under 18 years of age will not be admitted.<br />\n<br />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '2010-04-27 12:57:32', '2010-05-14 16:34:19'),
