(777, 'Film_title~A RARE GEM with Bunna Lawrie ~Month_completed~October~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~14~Film_running_seconds~00~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Kerri-Lee Harding ~Director~Kerri-Lee Harding ~Screenwriter~Kerri Lee Harding ~Director_of_Photography~Kerri Lee Harding ~Production_Designer~Kerri Lee Harding ~Sound_Recordist~Monica McDonald~Editor~Peter Worland / kerri-lee HArding ~Composer~Bunna Lawrie - Coloured Stone Band ~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Kerri-Lee Harinding / Bunna Lawrie ~Visual_Effects~Peter Worland ~Animator~n/a ~Other_Key_Crew~Adelw Wilkes ~Principal_Cast~Bunna Lawrie ~Genre~Documentary/~sypnosis~A RARE GEM - BUNNA LAWRIE Bunna Lawrie along with two of his brothers started out as a cover band playing small towns & Aboriginal missions across Australia. Bunna Lawrie is a highly respected Elder of the Mirning Aboriginal tribe from the Coastal Nullabor South Australia. Bunna is a Mirning Whale Dreamer + Songman Medicine man and story teller of his tribe. Legendary Aboriginal Rock band Coloured Stone was founded in 1977 by frontman Bunna Lawrie on the Kooniba Aboriginal Mission in South Australia. 1984 saw the the band record their very first single and  Black Boy  instant success. This tune is arguably an Aboriginal Australian rock n roll anthem. This short film tells the true uncensored version of events as we tell the story of these proud humble and one of a kind Aussie musicians whom sadly at times felt denied a place in the landscape that is Australia''s magical musical landscape.~publicity~THE COLOURED STONE BAND A RARE GEMBunna Lawrie A Rare Gem a short documentary film in 2013 was commissioned by NITV / SBS TV. This film is the Directorial debut of Kerri-Lee Harding (Hegarty) who has worked as a Radio Producer / Presenter with ABC RADIO and 3KND RADIO 1503AM and as a TV Researcher with Renegade Films on ''The History of Mining in Australia'' a 3 x part Documentary series screened in January 2013 on SBS Television. Most recently with Contact Films in the role of the Indigenous Archival Researcher on the 4 x part Documentary series....FIRST FOOTPRINTS in association with ABC Television and ARTE France.~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~Yes~education_institution~Open Channel ~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~Yes~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~Yes~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~Yes~Principal_first_name~Kerri-lee ~Principal_last_name~harding ~Principal_position~Director / Producer ~Principal_production_company~YALARRY INDIGMA MEDIA ~Principal_address~513/150 Brunswick street ~Principal_suburb~Fitzroy ~Principal_state~VIC~Principal_postcode~3065~Telephone_business_hours~96261738~Telephone_after_hours~n/a ~Principal_mobile~0458649661~Principal_fax~n/a ~email_private~kerri-leeharding@hotmail.com~email_public~kerri-leeharding@hotmail.com~Screening_ratio~16:9 Full Height Anamorphic (FHA) *preferred~screening_ratio_other~~Screening_format~Harddrive~Audio_specifications~Stereo~return_address~513/150 Brunswick street ~return_suburb~Fitzroy ~return_state~VIC~return_postcode~3065~payment_option~cheque or money order~entry_form~shortfilm~', '2014-01-21 18:58:32', ''),
