(732, 'Film_title~GRANDAD~Month_completed~November~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~7~Film_running_seconds~30~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Zyra McAuliffe~Director~Jonathon Dutton~Screenwriter~Andrew B Smith~Director_of_Photography~Greg de Marigny~Production_Designer~Ben Bangay~Sound_Recordist~Dane Cody~Editor~Jonathon Dutton~Composer~Dmitri Golovko~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Dmitri Golovko~Visual_Effects~~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~~Principal_Cast~Ian Smith Kevin Harrington Toby Wallace Darci McDonald Katrina Mathers Carolyn Bock~Genre~Comedy/~sypnosis~A black comedy about joel a 16 year old boy waiting to take his long adored Bekky out on their first date. But first Joel must survive the bizarre hazing of her overprotective and under appreciated Grandad. The two men cross swords but ultimately learn the same lesson: whether you''re 16 or 76 your biggest challenge is always the same and it''s all about being the person you know you oughta be.~publicity~St Kilda film festival would be the world premiere of GRANDAD. Directors StatementThe story behind GRANDAD was born during a hilarious BBQ conversation with a friend and new father who was likely to have suitors at his door in 15 years time but clearly lacked the grunt to scare them off. Fortunately he has a twisted father in law who could do the job for him. As a young filmmaker passionate about telling entertaining stories with something to say that speaks to different generations GRANDAD unashamedly leapt out of this conversation and onto the page. As we saw our story evolve we knew that we had to find a terrific cast capable of pulling off not only the comedic tension but the reality underpinning our characters’ situations and the dilemmas that emerge when we’re dishonest with ourselves and others. Having directed Ian and Toby in the past I knew what they were capable of and we shared a great journey developing the characters’ and performances together. We then attracted an exceptional crew and key creatives who understood what we were trying to achieve and helped us find the best way to tell our black comedy… ribbed for your pleasure. KEY CASTRole of Grandad – Ian Smith An iconic Australian actor with over 50 years experience on screen and stage Ian is best known for his role as Harold on NEIGHBOURS.Role of Joel – Toby Wallace A talented young actor who has worked with Jonathon on the short film MATES and is the lead role in the upcoming feature film RETURN TO NIMS ISLAND.Role of Barry - Kevin Harrington A highly respected and prolific actor Kevin has delivered terrific performances in everything from SEACHANGE to UNDERBELLY TANGLE and CLIFFY~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~No~education_institution~~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~No~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~Yes~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~Byron Bay Film Festival~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~Jonathon ~Principal_last_name~Dutton~Principal_position~Director~Principal_production_company~ETI film~Principal_address~PO Box 1079~Principal_suburb~South Melbourne~Principal_state~VIC~Principal_postcode~3205~Telephone_business_hours~0407540520~Telephone_after_hours~0407540520~Principal_mobile~0407540520~Principal_fax~~email_private~jono@entertainthinkinspire.com~email_public~jono@entertainthinkinspire.com~Screening_ratio~16:9 Full Height Anamorphic (FHA) *preferred~screening_ratio_other~~Screening_format~Harddrive~Audio_specifications~Stereo~return_address~PO BOX 1079~return_suburb~South Melbourne~return_state~VIC~return_postcode~3205~payment_option~credit card~entry_form~shortfilm~', '2014-01-14 15:39:09', '102729'),
