(722, 'Film_title~Revelation~Month_completed~November~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~12~Film_running_seconds~36~where_film__was_made~SA~Producer~Russell Jenkins~Director~Russell Jenkins~Screenwriter~Russell Jenkins~Director_of_Photography~Daniel Pearson~Production_Designer~~Sound_Recordist~Travis Williamson~Editor~Maisie Fabry~Composer~Russell Jenkins~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Travis Williamson~Visual_Effects~David Kauschke~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~Khaliah Marro Kelly Allison~Principal_Cast~Damien Rieck Wayne Anthoney Stephen Goldsmith~Genre~Drama/~sypnosis~A priest from Ireland is left abandoned on a beach in 1850s Australia.    The whispering wind of an empty alien land rushes around him as he stares to the horizon awaiting rescue to no avail. To leave the beach and trek inland for civialisation becomes the only choice but between him and a warm hearth lay the cold and harsh winter landscapes of windswept plains and steep hill forests.   A journey with no destination in a place half a world away from normality. A struggle with faith mind and body in a place where mistakes are not forgiven food is scarce and fear is constant.    But the lord has a plan for all and within the feared lies salvation.~publicity~The films script was written over many months whilst I was studying at MAPS Film School from November 2012. The film was almost entirely funded out of my [Russell Jenkins] pocket with some investment coming from mostly family and friends via a crowdfunding campaign on pozible. The shoot was originally supposed to take five days but finally ended with six due to extreme weather. The entire shoot was hampered by weather everyday which was a blessing and a curse. It looked good but was hard to work in especially for a student extreme-low-budget production. The film was far beyond what anyone within MAPS had ever tried to achieve. A Period piece requiring period costumes (some of which need to be made from scratch) and props set in the wilderness in muddy 