(713, 'Film_title~Love Song Devotions~Month_completed~September~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~7~Film_running_seconds~~where_film__was_made~NSW~Producer~Amanda Hood~Director~Amanda Hood~Screenwriter~Amanda Hood~Director_of_Photography~Ashley Barron~Production_Designer~~Sound_Recordist~Mark Henderson~Editor~Matt Villa ASE~Composer~~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~~Visual_Effects~~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~Max Gersbach- Gaffer~Principal_Cast~Robbie McGregor Michelle Collins Michael Anderson Karina Bano~Genre~Comedy/~sypnosis~Love Song Devotions is the story of late night love DJ Raymond Lamour and how his falls apart when his wife leaves him.~publicity~Sydney-based Writer/ Producer/ Director Amanda Hood fresh out of the UCLA film school in Los Angeles wrote Love Song Devotions for Tropfest 2013 where it was shortlisted into the Top 80 films out of 700 entries. The goal in the pre-production process for LSD was to get the best possible actors crew and locations. With help from Casting Assistant Alexis Johns (Mullinars Agency) we were able to open a lot more doors in terms of accessing quality talent. Perhaps the most exciting surprise of the production was when A Lister Editor Matt Villa (The Water Diviner The Great Gatsby I Robot) agreed to come on board as Editor because he loved the script. Working with Matt was a huge learning experience for Amanda.We secured our first choices for all cast with actor Robbie McGregor aka the voice of SBS for 15 years agreeing to play the film''s star Raymond Lamour. Triple M Radio in Sydney kindly gave us a radio studio to film in overnight and Robbie McGregor loaned us his gorgeous vintage car for the day to film the sunrise driving scenes.Making Love Song Devotions was a reminder of how generous Australians can be with both companies and individuals getting behind us and our film. ~is_film_score~No~is_student_production~No~education_institution~~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Austral