(691, 'Film_title~SLEEPOVER LA~Month_completed~December~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~14~Film_running_seconds~33~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Nicole Disson~Director~Lily Baldwin~Screenwriter~Lily Baldwin and Andrea Claire Maio~Director_of_Photography~Austin Rhodes ~Production_Designer~Sonja Kroop~Sound_Recordist~Ryan Canestro ~Editor~Lily Baldwin~Composer~Mark degli Antoni ~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Kent Sparling ~Visual_Effects~Colin Kohler ~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~Katie Casey Costume Designer; Ben Hethcoat AD + Associate Producer~Principal_Cast~Nicole Disson Lily Baldwin Ebe Sievwright Vivian Bang~Genre~Drama/Experimental/~sypnosis~A hotel overnight: Two lonely women spend a night at The Standard Downtown LA.  But things aren''t exactly what they seem.  Serendipitous overlaps and a poolside burial leave each woman with more than they were looking for.  An eccentric cast stylized dance and a bold score weave a dark and luminous short film that revamps traditional narrative. ~publicity~Link to view the official trailer:  https://vimeo.com/82037808Sleepover LA won the 2013 award for the best Snipler or 30 second pitch at the NEW MEDIA FILM FESTIVAL in LA: https://vimeo.com/65328540Director: www.LilyBaldwin.comProducer: www.NicoleDisson.blogspot.com/LILY BALDWIN  is a filmmaker and dancer based in NYC whose films use dance and gesture in stylized dreamscapes to drive narrative. Working with an array of musicians designers and visual artists she reinterprets conventional storytelling to make elegant and brash films. Her recent dance thriller Sea Meadow (SXSW 2012 Art Basel Miami 2013 BEST OF SXSW at St. Kilda''s Film Festival 30th anniversary Australia 2013) is available worldwide through Shorts International. Her previous films have screened internationally at festivals art fairs and Lincoln Center in NYC. Her work is featured on LE BOOK in affiliation with StudioProject of Stink Digital. Commercial work includes Coca Cola and Bloomingdale''s. Music videos include Blood Orange: Sutphin Boulevard The Forms: Fire To The Ground Cat Martino (Sufjan Stevens): Yr Not Alone. As a dancer she has performed with The Metropolitan Opera Ballet The Trisha Brown Dance Company among other NYC companies. Most recently she performed with David Byrne on the world tour for his album with Brian Eno Everything That Happens Will Happen Today and in its feature documentary Ride Rise Roar (SXSW 2011). More at:  www.lilybaldwin.com and www.seameadowthemovie.com NICOLE DISSON is a producer performer and curator who takes great pleasure in bringing people together to create and celebrate the arts. With a heavy theatre background and professional experience in brand and entertainment marketing Disson is recognized for her crossover work as a producer and performer and ability to cultivate talent while fusing this energy into unique settings and situations. Nicole conceived produced and performed in thirteen original showings of THE SERIES a multi-disciplinary production and event that cross-pollinates a social experience with the performing arts set on the rooftop of The Standard Downtown LA. She was the featured performer for the Soho House West Hollywood’s New Years Eve 2012 celebration and Director of Marketing and Associate Producer for Post Fact Production’s NEW. an experimental rock opera held at the historical 2500 seat Million Dollar Theater in Downtown LA.  Additionally she served as producer for artist Lita Albuquerque’s SPINE OF THE EARTH under The Getty Museum’s Pacific Standard Time Performance and Public Art Festival.  Nicole has performed in various theaters across the Nation including the world premiere of Frank Zappa’s musical JOE''S GARAGE at the Open First Theatre in Hollywood.  Originally from Washington D.C. Nicole now makes her home in Los Angeles.  More at: www.nicoledisson.blogspot.com~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~No~education_institution~~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~No~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~No~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~Nicole  ~Principal_last_name~Disson~Principal_position~Producer ~Principal_production_company~ND Productions ~Principal_address~1657 1/2 Golden Gate Ave. ~Principal_suburb~Los Angeles CA ~Principal_state~VIC~Principal_postcode~90026~Telephone_business_hours~1-202-276-5968~Telephone_after_hours~1-202-276-5968~Principal_mobile~~Principal_fax~~email_private~ndisson@gmail.com~email_public~ndisson@gmail.com~upload_ftp~yes~Screening_ratio~16:9 Full Height Anamorphic (FHA) *preferred~screening_ratio_other~~Screening_format~HDCam SR (25fps)~Audio_specifications~Dolby Surround~return_address~1657 1/2 Golden Gate Ave. ~return_suburb~Los Angeles CA ~return_state~VIC~return_postcode~90026~payment_option~credit card~entry_form~shortfilm~', '2014-01-06 08:04:11', '102681'),
