(659, 'Film_title~Nerds in Love~Month_completed~October~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~12~Film_running_seconds~00~where_film__was_made~NSW~Producer~Sean Rodrigo~Director~Sean Rodrigo~Screenwriter~Sean Rodrigo~Director_of_Photography~Evan Papageorgiou	 	~Production_Designer~~Sound_Recordist~Glenn Fitzpatrick	~Editor~Matt Osborne	~Composer~Ollie McGill~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Sonar Sound~Visual_Effects~Andy Noonan Kali Bateman Mike GibsonJohn Agapitos~Animator~Callan Woolcock~Other_Key_Crew~~Principal_Cast~Lawrence Leung Tessa De JosselinStan Walker~Genre~Drama/Comedy/~sypnosis~Nothing amazing ever happens to Emilio. Until one day while working night-shift as a cleaner in a shopping center he sees the girl of his dreams. ~publicity~25 year old Sydney based writer/director Sean Rodrigo said: “I wrote the film while I was at a real crossroads in my life working average jobs struggling with my career path wondering if I was ever going to make it as a filmmaker. But out of this challenging time came the inspiration for ‘Nerds in Love’ – afilm that’s essentially about hope and finding love and friendship in an unlikely situation; themes I’m sure the audience can relate to.”‘Nerds in Love’ is a classic (albeit quirky) story of romance: what happens when boymeets girl boy falls for girl – and the stupid things we do for love. What gives the film its quirky point of difference comes down not just to the casting storyline direction and production design it’s also where the story is set: a decidedly unromantic supermarket in a shopping mall.Sean explained: “After working at one of many soulless jobs I would trudge homethrough this local shopping centre and while it was rather depressing I remember thinking that it’d be a unique setting for a quirky story about two young people who aspire for something far greater in their lives – because that was something I was feeling at the time.”And so ‘Nerds in Love’ was born. With a quality script in hand which took him years to craft Sean leveraged off connections he’d made through freelance directing gigs and a stint at MTV to secure top tier acting and production talent for the film including: Melbourne Comedian Lawrence Leung (ABC and SBS) Stan Walker (Australian Idol winner 2009) and up and coming Sydney actress Tessa De Josselin as well as ‘Dumb Ways to Die’ composer and Cat Empire keyboardist and backing vocalist Ollie McGill – and post VFX and sound production by some of Australia’s best post houses: The Refinery Jumbla Engine Sonar Sound and FSM.Sean concluded with: “There’s a lot of uncertainty doubt and darkness in the world today and I love films that give you something good to hope for; films such as Jean-Pierre Jeunet’s ‘Amelie’ or Tiaka Wititi’s ‘Boy’ – great sources of inspiration to me – in which viewers are immersed in a world populated by optimistic themes and characters.~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~No~education_institution~~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~No~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~Yes~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~Flickerfest Melbourne Sydney~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~Sean~Principal_last_name~Rodrigo~Principal_position~Writer/Director~Principal_production_company~~Principal_address~17/131 Alice St~Principal_suburb~Newtown~Principal_state~NSW~Principal_postcode~2042~Telephone_business_hours~0405190851~Telephone_after_hours~0405190851~Principal_mobile~~Principal_fax~~email_private~sean@seanrodrigo.com~email_public~media@seanrodrigo.com~upload_ftp~yes~Screening_ratio~16:9 Full Height Anamorphic (FHA) *preferred~screening_ratio_other~~Screening_format~Secure FTP~Audio_specifications~Stereo~return_address~17/131 Alice st ~return_suburb~Newtown~return_state~NSW~return_postcode~2042~payment_option~credit card~entry_form~shortfilm~', '2013-12-17 21:24:01', '102651'),
