(602, 'Film_title~Sticky~Month_completed~October~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~19~Film_running_seconds~50~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Katrina Mazurek & Jilli Rose~Director~Jilli Rose~Screenwriter~Nicholas Carlile~Director_of_Photography~~Production_Designer~~Sound_Recordist~~Editor~~Composer~Kristin Rule & Billy Tankard~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Billy Tankard~Visual_Effects~~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~~Principal_Cast~~Genre~Animation/Documentary/Childrens/~sypnosis~Exiled from the tropical paradise where they evolved a handful of remarkable stick insects dodged extinction by hiding on a single windswept bush on the world''s tallest sea stack for 80 years. Now they live safely in captivity but when can they go home?~publicity~There are so many grim and worrying tales told in the conservation film genre. It''s easy to feel hopeless in the face of them. I''m such a fan of good news and the energising effects of an upbeat story. This story electrified me when I first read it. I was amazed that such a mind-blowing conservation success had happened right under my nose and I knew nothing about it. I instantly shelved the animation I was working on and started on pre-production for this film. ~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~No~education_institution~VIC~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~No~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~Yes~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~Flickerfest Byron Bay Revelation Perth MIAF~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~Jilli~Principal_last_name~Rose~Principal_position~Director &-Producer~Principal_production_company~Bespoke Animation~Principal_address~37 Urquhart Street~Principal_suburb~Castlemaine~Principal_state~VIC~Principal_postcode~3450~Telephone_business_hours~0401 427652~Telephone_after_hours~0401 427652~Principal_mobile~61401427652~Principal_fax~~email_private~producers@bespokeanimation.com~email_public~producers@bespokeanimatio