(600, 'Film_title~Off Course~Month_completed~March~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~8~Film_running_seconds~32~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Leo Baker~Director~Leo Baker~Screenwriter~Leo Baker~Director_of_Photography~Matt Wood~Production_Designer~~Sound_Recordist~Dane Cody~Editor~Leo Baker~Composer~Simon Walbrook~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~~Visual_Effects~William Gammon - CumulusVFX~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~~Principal_Cast~Adam Schmerl Kick Gurry Pier Carthew~Genre~Drama/~sypnosis~Two friends Chaz and Henry come across Ben an injured university student who has just been mugged. Chaz and Henry offer Ben a lift home that he gratefully accepts. Once in the car the two friends are more interested in learning about Ben than hearing his tales of woe. Things take a more serious turn when Chaz begins to interrogate Ben’s motivations for his university course and soon deepens to question his career choices and even his personal life. Ill-prepared and vulnerable Ben flounders under their sporting scrutiny and Chaz pushes Ben to reconsider these big decisions in his life.~publicity~Off Course is closely based off a true story. This is Leo''s first live action short film as writer / director since animating and editing the short film ''The Lost Thing'' which won best animated film at St Kilda Film Festival in 2011 as well as the Academy™ Award the same year.~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~No~education_institution~~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~No~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~Yes~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~Flickerfest~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~Leo~Principal_last_name~Baker~Principal_position~Director / Producer.~Principal_production_company~Roadknight Pictures~Principal_address~PO Box 1153~Principal_suburb~Fitzroy North~Principal_state~VIC~Principal_postcode~3068~Telephone_business_hours~0414 412 722~Telephone_after_hours~0414 412 722~Prin