(549, 'Film_title~The Game~Month_completed~August~Year_Completed~2012~Film_running_mins~10~Film_running_seconds~45~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Darian Szyszka~Director~Larelle Bossi~Screenwriter~Larelle Bossi & Darian Szyszka~Director_of_Photography~David Hawkins~Production_Designer~Larelle Bossi ~Sound_Recordist~Dan Haywood~Editor~Samantha Timmerman~Composer~Daniel Nixon~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Markus Kellow~Visual_Effects~~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~~Principal_Cast~John Flaus & Alan Hopgood~Genre~Drama/~sypnosis~A tale about foes the game of chess unravels male bravado to expose their ideas beliefs fears and at last the intimacy they share as friends.~publicity~The Game brings to life the friendship shared between the directors of Likerish Productions Larelle Bossi and Darian Szyszka. Darian an avid chess player and Larelle a master philosopher created Edward and Charles as a reflection of themselves. They took as its cue the symbolic complexity from the game the chess its pieces and the interaction of the board and strategy. Both John Flaus and Alan Hopgood are well respected actors on both screen and stage. They both fell in love with the script and agreed to play out the game in order to bring to life a more sentimental and philosophically awakening piece inspired  by a mature friendship.Likerish Productions has only just decided to release the film on the festival circuit. The Game has been invited to screen at the Bofa film festival (Nov 2013) where Larelle Bossi its award winning director will also be on a masterclass panel as well as in contention for the Entrepreneurial Spirit Award for 2013 - for her work in film both in Melbourne and more recently in Tasmania. The Game has its USA premiere at the Fort Lauderdale International Film Festival (Oct 2013) where it has been selected in competition. ~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~No~education_institution~~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~No~