(1040, 'Film_title~HUSH~Month_completed~February~Year_Completed~2014~Film_running_mins~8~Film_running_seconds~40~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Maia Horniak & Cath Moore~Director~Maia Horniak~Screenwriter~Cath Moore~Director_of_Photography~Jody Muston~Production_Designer~Jo Briscoe~Sound_Recordist~~Editor~Maia Horniak Julie Anne de Ruvo Que Minh Luu~Composer~Basil Hogios~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Michael Theiler~Visual_Effects~Melvin Montalban~Animator~Melvin Montalban~Other_Key_Crew~~Principal_Cast~Ishika Kinzel~Genre~Drama/Childrens/Experimental/~sypnosis~Being deaf is lonely for 9-year-old Ishika especially on weekend visits to her Father.  But when she steps into her special world of imagination nature offers a much needed companion who helps her understand that saying ‘I love you’ speaks volumes.~publicity~This film was made to be able to empathise and understand a young deaf girl and her unique world. The main actor Ishika Kinzel had never acted before and this is her first ever performance. She is not deaf and had learnt AUSLAN sign language from a mentor for several months prior to filming. The film was shot in Melbourne and most of the team are from Melbourne. We used a GoPro camera for her direct POV and achieved this method by strapping it to her head in various ways. The sound design and animation is treated in a unique way in order to step in and out of her imaginative yet ''deaf'' world. The production team were ALL women: there were only four on the crew for the shoot to keep it intimate for the child actor the crew were only the writer Director DOP and Designer. The man playing the young girls father is actually her real father and he has also never acted before. The film was very verité in its process and experimental in its post production. ~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~No~education_institution~Outside US or Canada~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~No~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~Yes~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~SFF MIFF~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~Maia~Principal_last_name~Horniak~Principal_position~~Principal_production_company~~Principal_address~14/20-24 Mansfield Ave. Caringbah~Principal_suburb~Sydney~Principal_state~NSW~Principal_postcode~2229~Telephone_business_hours~0431062980~Telephone_after_hours~0431062980~Principal_mobile~~Principal_fax~~email_private~maiahorniak@gmail.com~email_public~maiahorniak@gmail.com~Screening_ratio~16:9 Full Height Anamorphic (FHA) *preferred~screening_ratio_other~~Screening_format~Harddrive~Audio_specifications~Stereo~return_address~14/20-24 Mansfield Ave. Caringbah~return_suburb~Sydney~return_state~NSW~return_postcode~2229~payment_option~cheque or money order~entry_form~shortfilm~', '2014-03-13 17:09:33', ''),
(1041, 'Film_title~Life on Tape~Month_completed~November~Year_Completed~2013~Film_running_mins~7~Film_running_seconds~35~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~David Valkenet~Director~Oscar Strangio~Screenwriter~Oscar Strangio~Director_of_Photography~Jack Ralph~Production_Designer~~Sound_Recordist~Matthew Galvin~Editor~Oscar Strangio~Composer~Lewis Coleman~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~~Visual_Effects~~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~~Principal_Cast~John Flaus~Genre~Comedy/Documentary/~sypnosis~Life on Tape follows the obsession of John Flaus a well known Australian actor voice talent and film academic as he tries to document the world in its current state. Flaus records the world''s events by vigorously collecting daily newspaper articles and recording shows off television. After Forty years of collecting he has amassed rooms full of tapes papers and relevant documents. So what started this obsession where is it headed and what value can be attached to one man''s take on how the world is reported?~publicity~Life on Tape was selected to screen at the prestigious Melbourne Cinematheque as part of the 80th birthday celebration for John Flaus where it was met with an overwhelmingly positive audience. ~is_film_score~Yes~is_student_production~Yes~education_institution~Swinburne University~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~No~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~Yes~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~Yes~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~Sydney Film Festival Antenna Documentary Film Festival~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~David~Principal_last_name~Valkenet~Principal_position~Producer~Principal_production_company~Point Cool Productions~Principal_address~1 Glenroy Road~Principal_suburb~Hawthorn~Principal_state~VIC~Principal_postcode~3122~Telephone_business_hours~0448776560~Telephone_after_hours~0448776560~Principal_mobile~0448776560~Principal_fax~~email_private~davidvalkenet@gmail.com~email_public~davidvalkenet@gmail.com~upload