(1056, 'Film_title~Head Space~Month_completed~October~Year_Completed~2014~Film_running_mins~2~Film_running_seconds~44~where_film__was_made~VIC~Producer~Fraser Cameron~Director~Fraser Cameron~Screenwriter~Fraser Cameron~Director_of_Photography~~Production_Designer~~Sound_Recordist~~Editor~Fraser Cameron~Composer~~Post_Prod_Sound/Sound_Design~Fraser Cameron~Visual_Effects~~Animator~~Other_Key_Crew~Darcy Tuppen~Principal_Cast~Darcy Tuppen Seamus Gleeson Carl Tolley Fraser Cameron~Genre~Experimental/~sypnosis~Inspired largely by an idea that we are all finding ourselves in a world filled with chaotic sounds and situations inevitable in a 21st century city. We are subjected to this day in day out and only find time to ourselves when we are home. Each person has their own way to ‘get away’ from the world when they are alone in an environment controlled by them. This work shows the different ways in which we escape whether it is by the music we listen to the television shows we watch or the music we play. We are all different in a world where differentiating yourself can be difficult.    ~publicity~Each individual is conducting an act in their own bedroom every situation unique to them. Each asked what they do when they get home to their room when no-one else is around.~is_film_score~No~is_student_production~Yes~education_institution~Deakin University~this_entry_to_be_a_Victorian_Premiere~Yes~screened_or_broadcast_publicly_in_Australia~Yes~intend_to_enter_any_other_Australian_film_festivals~No~other_Australian_film_festivals_intent_to_enter~~by_Aboriginal_filmmakers~No~Principal_first_name~Fraser~Principal_last_name~Cameron~Principal_position~Director Editor DOP~Principal_production_company~~Principal_address~140 Earlsfield Drive~Principal_suburb~Berwick~Principal_state~VIC~Principal_postcode~3806~Telephone_business_hours~+61 403084986~Telephone_after_hours~+61 403084986~Principal_mobile~~Principal_fax~~email_private~frasercameron93@yahoo.com~email_public~frasercameron93@y